============================================================
with sharing | without sharing | inherited sharing
============================================================

These keywords control Record-Level Security in Apex.

They DO NOT control:
- Object-Level Security (CRUD)
- Field-Level Security (FLS)

They only control:
- Record-Level Security

============================================================
1. with sharing
============================================================

Definition
- Executes Apex by respecting the current user's record access.

Result
- User can access only the records they are allowed to see.

Syntax

public with sharing class AccountService {

}

Example

OWD for Account = Private

Admin owns:
- Account A
- Account B

Sales User owns:
- Account C

Code

List<Account> accs = [SELECT Name FROM Account];

Result

Admin
Returns:
A
B
C

Sales User
Returns:
C

Reason
The class respects sharing rules.

Use When
- Lightning Controllers
- REST APIs
- Aura/LWC Controllers
- Business logic accessed by users
- Almost all application code

============================================================
2. without sharing
============================================================

Definition
- Ignores Record-Level Sharing.

Result
- Runs in System Context.

Syntax

public without sharing class AccountService {

}

Example

OWD = Private

Admin owns:
A
B

Sales User owns:
C

Query

SELECT Name FROM Account

Result

Admin
A
B
C

Sales User
A
B
C

Reason
Sharing rules are ignored.

Important

without sharing DOES NOT bypass

- CRUD Permissions
- Field Level Security

Those must still be enforced separately.

Use When

- Admin Utilities
- Background Processing
- Data Migration
- Batch Jobs
- Trusted Internal Processes

============================================================
3. inherited sharing
============================================================

Definition

The class inherits the sharing mode of the calling class.

Syntax

public inherited sharing class AccountService {

}

Scenario 1

Controller

public with sharing class Controller

↓

Calls

public inherited sharing class Service

Result

Runs WITH sharing.

------------------------------------------------------------

Scenario 2

Controller

public without sharing class Controller

↓

Calls

public inherited sharing class Service

Result

Runs WITHOUT sharing.

------------------------------------------------------------

Reason

The Service class follows whatever sharing mode the caller uses.

Use When

Reusable service classes.

